commentary: Junaid Khan to DM Bravo, OUT appeal for catch at the wicket, not given and they have immediately reviewed it. And it's not just Junaid and Akmal, even Hafeez wants the review. Short of a length, angling in, Bravo is not behind the line as he defends. There is a clear sound as the ball passes the outside edge, but there is no obvious deviation. Bravo, a walker from whatever cricket I have seen him play, is not pleased with this. Seriously we don't have enough technology here to operate proper DRS. He has given him out based on sound alone. Bravo is left to shake his head
shortText: Junaid Khan to DM Bravo, OUT
text: appeal for catch at the wicket, not given and they have immediately reviewed it. And it's not just Junaid and Akmal, even Hafeez wants the review. Short of a length, angling in, Bravo is not behind the line as he defends. There is a clear sound as the ball passes the outside edge, but there is no obvious deviation. Bravo, a walker from whatever cricket I have seen him play, is not pleased with this. Seriously we don't have enough technology here to operate proper DRS. He has given him out based on sound alone. Bravo is left to shake his head

commentary: Junaid Khan to Sammy, 2 runs short, into the body, pulled away to deep midwicket. Sammy wants the second, and has nearly made a non-existent run. Sammy thinks he is gone, but replays show the throw was a bit full and it took Akmal a split-second extra to flick the bail off, and Sammy is super quick. In one frame his bat is on the line and the bail is coming off, but the third umpire doesn't count it as the bail fully dislodged. In the next frame, Sammy is in. He is surprised he is not out

commentary: Sammy to Ahmed Shehzad, OUT Shehzad has sold his mate down the river. Played from deep inside the crease, he starts running for a single, only to realise he has hit it too close to Gayle at square leg. Now he sends Jamshed back, and his only chance is an error from West Indies. He almost gets it. Gayle lobs the ball back towards the non-striker's end, Sammy runs back to collect, but seems to have lost the ball. Somehow, though, the throw is a direct hit

commentary: Best to Misbah-ul-Haq, no run this is getting reviewed for a strangle down the leg side. Not given out on the field. Short of a length, into the ribs, Misbah plays at it, looking to tuck it away into the leg side. The ball as it passes Misbah is awfully close to the glove. And there is a deviation. So if it has hit anything, it is the glove. The same Bravo argument in the morning should stand here. Remember we don't have HotSpot. In this case, the umpires feel there is enough doubt to not overturn the on-field call. Best and Bravo and Sammy are gutted. Best asks questions of Umpire Reiffel. Bravo stands stunned
